## VI, 142. Blessing during the sowing of seed.

1\. Raise thyself up, grow thick by thy own might, O grain! Burst every
vessel! The lightning in the heavens shall not destroy thee!  
2. When we invoke thee, god grain, and thou dost listen, then do thou
raise thyself up like the sky, be inexhaustible as the sea!  
3. Inexhaustible shall be those that attend to thee, inexhaustible thy
heaps! Theywhogivethee as a present shall be inexhaustible, they who eat
thee shall be inexhaustible!

